# RDF 3.3.1 Release Notes

## 3.3.1

-- Changes --

[Remove] Agent-Teams triad (3.2 T5 debt cleanup): the deprecated v2 dispatch
      modules (lib/dispatch.sh, lib/cmd/dispatch.sh) and their `rdf dispatch` CLI
      route in bin/rdf, the two design specs (dispatch-abstraction.md,
      task-based-coordination.md), and adapters/claude-code/teams-meta.json; v3
      runs plans through the dispatcher agent and RDF's 2026-04-21 harness
      research rejected Agent Teams as tool-locked (the JSON registries these
      consumed were already removed)
[Remove] lib/rdf_common.sh rdf_profile_includes() — an unconditional `return 0`
      stub since v3 dropped profile.json filtering; also dropped its one live
      caller (the cc_generate_scripts profile gate in the claude-code adapter),
      which never fired, so all scripts still generate unchanged
[Remove] lib/rdf_common.sh dead helpers rdf_feature_enabled() (orphaned by the
      dispatch.sh removal) and rdf_json_get() (zero callers; audit finding I3
      confirmed)
[Remove] profiles/registry.md "Starter Profiles" tombstone section (all profiles
      were promoted to the full tier)
[Remove] RDF.md teams-meta.json / dispatch.sh tree entries and the "Agent Teams
      API instability" risk row — they documented the now-retired architecture

## 3.3.0

-- New Features --

[New] claude-plugin adapter (fifth target): generates a Claude Code plugin with
      namespace-rewritten commands (/r-X → /rdf:r-X), agent/script/hook output,
      CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT hook paths, and a VERSION-stamped plugin.json; the repo
      declares itself a marketplace with committed output so `/plugin marketplace
      add rfxn/rdf` + `/plugin install rdf@rdf` work with no build step
[New] install-mode detection: `rdf doctor` reports symlink vs plugin install and
      `rdf deploy` warns when both coexist (dual-install drift)
[New] CI plugin job — generate, content-drift check, and strict marketplace
      validation on every push
[New] LICENSE (GNU GPL v2), community health files (CODE_OF_CONDUCT, CONTRIBUTING,
      SECURITY), and a public ROADMAP.md
[New] GitHub Pages landing, 5-minute quickstart, recorded demo in the README first
      fold, social-preview card, and a privacy-policy page for verified plugin
      status
[New] tests/state-injection.bats and tests/cmd-migrate-init.bats — regression
      coverage for state-script code injection and the migrate/init upgrade paths

-- Bug Fixes --

[Fix] SECURITY: state/context-audit.sh code injection → RCE — a git commit message
      containing ''' broke out of the json.loads('''...''') triple-quoted python
      string, so /r-context-audit crawling any workspace repo executed
      attacker-controlled code; state JSON now flows to python via stdin/argv and
      _json_str escapes \r/\t (untrusted repo metadata → code execution)
[Fix] first-run hardening: drop hardcoded /root paths and rfxn-workspace
      assumptions from doctor, migrate, CLI output, and docs; a missing README on a
      target project is now WARN, not FAIL
[Fix] tests/plugin-adapter.bats deploy-warn test uses a hermetic fixture RDF_HOME
      (CI has no committed claude-code output to lean on)

-- Changes --

[Change] canonical/scripts/context-bar.sh — parse the hook input JSON once (five jq
         calls → one) and the transcript once for token totals and turn count (was
         two slurps sharing a filter); output is byte-identical, cutting per-tick
         subprocesses on the statusline hot path
[Change] state/git-hooks/pre-commit — batch the anti-pattern scan: prefilter
         #-suppressed lines once per file, then one grep per class instead of an
         echo|grep per added line per class; findings are byte-identical
[Change] command-prefix bare coreutils in first-party source (lib/cmd/deploy.sh,
         the claude-code/codex/gemini-cli adapters, post-edit-lint.sh,
         pre-commit-validate.sh) for el6 PATH portability
[Change] CLAUDE.md — scope the suppression-comment rule to new/modified
         suppressions (enforced by pre-commit on added lines); note the
         vendored-script advisory boundary
[Change] README and docs — reposition for broad public adoption, correct the
         command inventory, add measured-impact stats, and rebuild the Pages site

## 3.2.1

-- Changes --

[Change] tests/governance-contracts.bats — the reviewer challenge/sentinel
         contract anchors to the mode headers (^### Challenge Mode / ^### Sentinel
         Mode) instead of bare prose mentions, so it bites if a mode section is
         gutted or renamed (post-3.2.0 review follow-up)
[Change] state/context-audit.sh — find -printf capability probe targets /dev/null
         (target-independent, avoids a false BSD-branch selection); GNU and BSD
         byte-sum branches use the same ! -type d predicate as the file count

## 3.2.0

-- New Features --

[New] tests/governance-contracts.bats — behavioral-contract eval harness: 13
      contracts assert the evidence-discipline chain (engineer, dispatcher, qa,
      reviewer, /r-review-answer, /r-verify-claim, orchestration default) still
      lives in canonical source, so a prompt edit that silently drops a contract
      fails CI instead of shipping; closes the eval-driven-development gap
[New] lib/rdf_common.sh: rdf_hash_stdin — portable digest resolver (sha256sum →
      shasum -a 256 → sha1sum); adapter.sh and doctor.sh route hashing through it
[New] canonical/reference/simplicity-budget.md — earn-the-surface rule and
      when-NOT-to-orchestrate doctrine (serial default; parallel fan-out is a
      ~15x bet reserved for provably breadth-first work)

-- Bug Fixes --

[Fix] macOS/BSD portability completion (T1): rdf generate no longer aborts on
      stock macOS (sha256sum-or-die → shasum -a 256 fallback); stat -c → BSD
      stat -f (mtime/size no longer report 0), find -printf byte-sum fallback,
      statusline md5sum → md5 -q, and templated mktemp across setup, clone,
      half-clone, migrate, and test-half-clone

-- Changes --

[Change] canonical/agents/dispatcher.md — Execute defaults to the least
         machinery; parallel only for provably-independent phases
[Change] canonical/agents/reviewer.md — challenge-mode check 3: a plan adding a
         command/agent/mode/profile/gate/rule must state the behavior it changes
[Change] CLAUDE.md.ref (+ regenerated AGENTS.md) — Scope Discipline gains the
         earn-the-surface rule

## 3.1.4

-- New Features --

[New] canonical/commands/r-review-answer.md — route each sentinel/challenge
      finding to a structured FIX / REBUT / DEFER response and write a
      .rdf/work-output/sentinel-N-answer artifact; advisory only (no merge
      gate); reuses /r-verify-claim for evidence and flags unanswered MUST-FIX
      and evidence-free REBUT

-- Changes --

[Change] canonical/commands/r-spec.md §2.2 Step A — research now probes
         external/runtime unknowns (binary paths, protocol/auth shapes,
         install-environment footprints) via one-liners or /r-verify-claim,
         folding results into the spec as facts rather than assumptions
[Change] canonical/reference/framework.md, canonical/commands/r-review.md —
         document the sentinel-N-answer artifact and point /r-review at
         /r-review-answer

## 3.1.3

-- New Features --

[New] lib/rdf_common.sh — rdf_canonical_path portable symlink-resolving path
      helper (readlink -f → realpath → cd -P fallback); doctor.sh adopts it
      in place of a bare readlink -f
[New] tests/portability.bats plus rdf_uuidv7 portability cases in
      rdf-bus.bats; CI test matrix gains a macOS leg exercising system bash
      3.2 and BSD coreutils

-- Bug Fixes --

[Fix] bin/rdf — resolve RDF_HOME through PATH symlinks via a depth-bounded
      BASH_SOURCE loop (bash 3.2-safe, no readlink -f); fixes deterministic
      startup ENOENT on macOS/Homebrew and /usr/local scattered layouts
      (contributed by ggwicz)
[Fix] state/rdf-bus.sh — rdf_uuidv7 portable millisecond cascade
      (EPOCHREALTIME → date +%s%N when numeric → date +%s + RANDOM); no
      longer aborts under set -e on BSD/older macOS where date +%s%N is
      non-numeric
[Fix] .github/workflows/ci.yml — remove the job-level hashFiles() guard on the
      tests job; job-level if is evaluated before checkout, which GitHub
      rejects as a workflow-file error — CI had failed at startup (0 jobs) on
      every run since it was introduced in 3.0.5
[Fix] tests/adapter.bats — post-generate doctor test now scopes to
      content-drift; full doctor's sync/github/memory checks FAIL in a clean
      CI checkout and would have failed the now-running suite

-- Changes --

[Change] lib/cmd/refresh.sh, state/rotate-work-output.sh — guard the
         rdf-bus.sh source and fail with an actionable message instead of a
         raw ENOENT when the bus helper is absent

## 3.1.2

-- New Features --

[New] state/rdf-bus.sh — rdf_active_plan_path / rdf_set_active_plan /
      rdf_clear_active_plan resolver with three-tier fallback (session
