      via git rm --cached; file retained on disk as legacy fallback

**Operator note:** Existing clones may have `docs/` blanket-ignored in
`.git/info/exclude` (added pre-3.1.2). For `/r-plan` to commit new
plans into `docs/plans/`, remove that line: `sed -i '/^docs\/$/d'
.git/info/exclude`. Verify with `git check-ignore docs/plans/test.md`
(expect exit 1).

## 3.1.1 — Reviewer ROI Improvements

This release targets the three most frequent classes of findings absorbed
by the reviewer in the blacklight corpus (~106 distinct findings across
53 build stops, ~11.7 active reviewer-hours). By moving detection earlier
— to the planner, the pre-commit hook, and the engineer setup step — the
reviewer spends cycles on novel issues rather than recurring hygiene.

**Area A: Plan Validation**

Two new checks run before the reviewer ever sees a plan. Rule 9 in
`plan-schema.md` counts `@test` blocks in the declared test suite and
compares the count against any assertion in the phase text ("expect N
tests after this phase"). A mismatch is a hard failure. Rule 9 is
conditional: phases that make no count assertion are not checked. Planner
Step 1.5 pins RC-contract evidence in the plan preamble — for every
caller-helper-fn referenced in the plan, the planner reads the helper's
source, extracts expected return codes, and pastes a per-call-site table.
Both checks run at `/r-plan` Step 2.7 and `/r-build` §1; the reviewer
Challenge Mode verifies their presence.

**Area B: Scope-Aware Sentinel**

The reviewer sentinel now accepts a `target-class` signal (`prose`,
`code`, `schema`, or `mixed`) that adjusts default severity ladders by
pass. Prose reviews deprioritize anti-slop; schema reviews prioritize
structural constraint checks. The dispatcher derives `target-class`
automatically from phase file extensions and passes it in the dispatch
payload. An Early-Exit rubric skips Pass 3 when Passes 1 and 2 are
clean, the diff is under 300 lines, and no security-flagged files are
in scope — reducing over-deployment of full sentinel on trivial diffs.

This release also caps the full sentinel at 3 passes (Pass 4 Performance
was dropped). The verdict marker `passes_3_4_skipped` is renamed to
`pass_3_skipped`. The target-class default is `code`, which preserves
prior 3-pass behavior on all existing dispatches that do not specify
target-class.

**Area C: Build-Time Hygiene + Boundary-Guard**

The pre-commit hook (introduced in Wave A) gains an anti-pattern grep
section that runs after the existing scope check. Five pattern classes
are covered: bare coreutils without `command` prefix, `/tmp` paths
constructed with `$$` or `$RANDOM`, `2>/dev/null` and `|| true` without
a same-line justification comment, tombstone phrases (`replaces ... stub`,
`was: ...`, `# removed:`), and `local var=$(...)` rc-mask. A same-line
`#` comment suppresses any finding. Projects opt-out per class via
`# anti-pattern-skip: <class>` in `governance/ignore.md`.

Engineer Setup now includes step 7 (boundary-guard sweep) for
`scope:cross-cutting` and `scope:sensitive` phases. The engineer greps
schema directories for input fields lacking `pattern`, `enum`, or `format`
constraints, cross-references against call-site sinks (filesystem paths,
shell commands, JSONL appends), and pastes the result table into EVIDENCE.
Step 7 short-circuits with an INFO marker when no schema files are in
scope; it does not run on `scope:focused` or narrower phases.

**`/r-util-claudemd-review` Primitive**

A new utility command provides a structured review of CLAUDE.md files.
Adapted from ykdojo/claude-code-tips `review-claudemd` and extended with
RDF-specific discipline filters (D1 — no prose/narrative, D2 — no
memory-bound state, D3 — no framework default restatement, D4 — no
tone/sentiment). The filters apply to both the subagent's recommendations
and the audit of existing CLAUDE.md content.

**Backwards Compatibility**

All changes are additive or conditional:
- Rule 9 fires only when a count assertion is present; existing plans
  without count assertions are unaffected.
- `target-class` defaults to `code`, preserving current 3-pass sentinel
  behavior on dispatches that do not specify the class.
- Pre-commit hook anti-pattern checks opt-in per project via
  `governance/ignore.md`; projects without that file receive the full
  check, which reflects the codebase conventions documented in the parent
  CLAUDE.md.

